  "riddle": "1. Unearth the career of the cricketer whose name echoes through the annals of Australian sports. How many Test matches adorned his legacy?\n\n2. To continue your journey, distill your previous number down to its essence. What does the digital root reveal when you sum its digits repeatedly until a single digit remains?\n\n3. A rich genre arose beneath the Southern Cross — find the count of distinct musical \"waves\" that made their mark from 1955 to 1975 in this sunburnt land.\n\n4. How high does this celebrated formation rise above the sea level? Seek the elevation that defines the heights of this cultural landmark.\n\n5. Explore the travelers' judgment of this geological wonder. What star rating does it receive from those who have journeyed to its embrace?\n\n6. With your combined wisdom from the previous clues, calculate the absolute difference between the elevation you discovered in clue 4 and the star rating from clue 5.\n\n7. In the spirit of thoroughness, retrieve the elevation of the celebrated landmark once again — how high does it soar above sea level?\n\n8. Whose melodies captured the hearts of many? Journey to the ensemble whose founding figures crafted their sound in the late '70s. How many core members emerged to shape this iconic band?\n\n9. With the knowledge acquired, compute the absolute difference between the elevation found in clue 4 and the star rating in clue 5. What remains when you take that number modulo 10? \n\nRemember, your final answer will be a single digit between 0 and 9, crafted through the wisdom gleaned from clues 4, 5, and 6.",
